        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 26 at 12:57AM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 1256 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 4
miles southeast of Mocksville, or near Cooleemee, moving south at 20
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Salisbury, Mocksville, Spencer, Cooleemee, Fork Church, Piedmont
Research Station, and Woodleaf.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
